cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with computing rate regions in network coding using entropy function region algorithms. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses multi-source network coding instances. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the interpretation of the network symmetry group as a group of symmetries of a polyhedron and the use of techniques for exploiting symmetry in polyhedral computation. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes an algorithm for computing polyhedral outer bounds on rate regions. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also relevant as the paper discusses the use of the Convex Hull Method, which is a well-known algorithm in computational geometry.
